website_summaries.verdict: Great pick for storing rakes, shovels and outdoor tools that are awkward to keep elsewhere.
pros: Garden shed with 17 cubic foot capacity
Durable construction, with double wall design and a floor that resists impacts
Handles designed to accommodate a lock
cons: Good for storage of large objects, but lack of shelving is limiting

customer_reviews.title: Found shelves.......
customer_reviews.text: This does not come with shelves, I am a widow and have no way to fabricate them. I found them on Uline, for Slim Jim model, part # H5926. Affordable, can figure out why they don't offer them with the unit.
customer_reviews.author: Jeanette Fox

customer_reviews.title: Excellent and very sturdy
customer_reviews.text: Excellent and very sturdy. Many comments about lack of supplied shelves and difficulty in fabrication; go to a web site for company called ULine which sells the shelves (they refer to the shed as their Slim Jim model). Shelves are sturdy, fit perfectly and are reasonably priced. For those who say the shed is not sturdy, their shed was probably not assembled correctly--must make sure the inter-locking tabs are fully seated which requires a mallet.
customer_reviews.author: PHILIP R. COWEN

customer_reviews.title: Nice shed with cedar shelves
customer_reviews.text: It is a nice small shed for your garden tools. Assembly was very quick and easy. I made four shelves out of a 1" x 10" by 10 foot long rough cut cedar board from Lowe's that I bought for about $35. Cedar is weather and termite resistant. I added a little bit to the length and depth of each shelf that was recommended in the instruction sheet. My shelves are 28.625" x 9.50". The corners of the back of the shelves were cut off using 3.375" instead of the 3.19" recommended in the instruction sheet. The shelves fit perfectly. There is plenty of room in front of the shelves for your tall tools and items to stand upright.
customer_reviews.author: John D. Smith

customer_reviews.title: Good small storage works well on a porch
customer_reviews.text: Nice vertical cabinet. For less than 20.00 added shelf’s If you don’t want to cut your own shelf uline has precut shelf’s. Look under Slim Jim storage. If you have a saw ,save your money and cut your own only takes minutes.
customer_reviews.author: Luther

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy and EASY to assemble!
customer_reviews.text: PROS: Will fit on my balcony and provided extra storage that I need! I'm a 67 year old woman with a bad back and I had no problems assembling this by myself.... just follow directions. : ) CONS: I would like Rubbermaid to offer ready made shelves and hooks for this storage unit again! Why were they discontinued!? I cannot custom make shelves myself as I don't have the tools and will not have place to store them... nor do I see a need for more tools at this point. : ) PLEASE offer ready made shelves again!
customer_reviews.author: Maggie

customer_reviews.title: Poor Quality!
customer_reviews.text: Boy Amazon you certainly misrepresented this product as relates to its size. The headline description stated it to be 2' x 2'. This is not the true size and so it does not fit my allotted space. Shame on me or not reading the small print. It also is of disappointing quality, especially the door lock. A two year old could easily break it open! Would not recommend this product to anyone. Also should mention it took two tries to get it here in one piece. First order came with holes punched in it from what appeared to be forklift tines,crushing parts of the back wall and floor.
customer_reviews.author: sharon kay wright

customer_reviews.title: There were two problems with this item. First of ...
customer_reviews.text: There were two problems with this item. First of all, the roof was warped so that it was not possible to attach the side as directions indicated. However, that didn't end up the main problem. The ad shows that the product is 30 inches wide. The location where I was going to place it is 31 inches wide. In fact, the top of this is 32 inches wide. It indicated that it is 25 inches deep but it appeared that the interior would only be 21 inches deep. I am not confident of that measurement as I was never able to assemble it.
customer_reviews.author: sparkie

customer_reviews.title: Nice Shed.. bad description on Amazon webpage! FOUR shelves Only.
customer_reviews.text: The shed itself was easy to put together, and seems like it will be very sturdy. I have no issues with the shed directly, it's exactly as pictured.. however the descriptions in multiple places here say it has "grooves for 5 shelves". That is incorrect. This model only had grooves for FOUR shelves. I don't know how it was typed in multiple places incorrectly, but my guess is the measurements, and description are probably for an older model Rubbermaid sold. Just know it has FOUR shelves, not Five and you'll probably love the shed. We'll see how it holds up over time, but since it's in my covered patio, I expect it to last quite a while.
customer_reviews.author: Jordan Petlev

customer_reviews.title: Outstanding, in Florida we've had strong winds and rain ...
customer_reviews.text: Outstanding, in Florida we've had strong winds and rain, it didn't not get wet on the inside..my husband is going to add shevles for me..now my hose will be kept much more neatly...
customer_reviews.author: N. Wigsten

customer_reviews.title: This shed was bad from Day 1
customer_reviews.text: This shed was bad from Day 1. I thought it was pricey, but bought it because I thought Rubbermaid would make a good, sturdy product. It did not go together well, and I could never get all the pieces to snap correctly. My wife and I struggled with it for over a year - always trying to get the pieces snapped in correctly. Finally, in a fit of fury, my wife pulled it apart and threw it away. Waste of money!!!
customer_reviews.author: George Cunningham

customer_reviews.title: Simple to assemble
customer_reviews.text: I was happily surprised by the ease of assembly. Other than a RUBBER MALLET (works best) no tools needed. Seems tight fitting and solid. One side note, there's a slight learning curve in assembling the sections. There's no need to slide the sections all the way from the beginning point. Usually two or three inches of forward progress is required to lock the joints.
customer_reviews.author: J. Smith

customer_reviews.title: Great little narrow shed for small spaces!!
customer_reviews.text: Great shed that does t take up much room. We needed a shed for a small space and it was perfect. We are using it for garden tools and shovels etc that stand vertically. It does not have shelves so don’t expect them. Perfect for our needs. Easy to rinse out and keep clean.
customer_reviews.author: Good customer!

customer_reviews.title: JUST WHAT I NEEDED TO STORE MY BROOMS
customer_reviews.text: The package was delivered with some damage to the box but the storage shed was not damaged. it was very heavy to move so I had to open the box where it was delivered and removed each piece. It came in 7 pieces and each piece was very light weight to handle. Each piece just snaps into each other with a soft mallet. It is very sturdy, does not wobble. There are grooves to add shelving or to store tall items such as brooms or shovels.
customer_reviews.author: Linda V

customer_reviews.title: Very easy to pop this together with no tools
customer_reviews.text: This is the easiest assembly ever by myself with no tools needed. We will see how it weathers but it seems quite sturdy to me. I put it together on the ground, stood it up and "walked" it to where I wanted it with nothing pulling apart. Then, after reading shelf comments, I put a 5 shelf wire rack in there that leaves a few inches on one side for tall handled items. I put a ceramic tile under each rack leg to protect the floor in case all that weight on little peg feet could deform the plastic floor of the shed.
customer_reviews.author: Maxie

customer_reviews.title: Just what I wanted, but not appropriate for industrial use
customer_reviews.text: This is a small cabinet, which is exactly what I wanted. It’s just the right height, depth and width for the space that I needed it for. Very easy to put together with two people. One person could probably do it, but it might be a struggle. I am looking for the shelves to put in it now. I wouldn’t recommend this for frequent or industrial use, as it’s simply not built for that.
customer_reviews.author: Laurie Keve

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble, but then screw pieces togethker
customer_reviews.text: After you get it set up, you’ll want to buy some 1-1/2 inch wood screws and with your electric drill - hold those pop-in places, in place. Otherwise, the 1st time you try to move it, you’ll be starting from the beginning trying to pop it back together.
customer_reviews.author: John F. Schafer

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for my needs
customer_reviews.text: A "tad" expensive but it is a quality Rubbermade item. I like the overall design and the roofline. I did purchase the wooden shelving from Uline - they fit perfectly. And I purchased a lock. I am keeping overflow household items in this shed on my deck. I have a small mobile home and inside storage doesn't accomodate storing when I want to stock up sometimes.
customer_reviews.author: BoomBoom

customer_reviews.title: Almost perfect.
customer_reviews.text: If the joints had some mechanism to secure them together, this storage unit would be great. However, someone can just come up to it and rip the roof off. Meaning the lock latch is pointless. I also had to drill it to make the lock latch hole fit a normal sized lock. Other than it, the plastic molded pieces are solid and should last a long time.
customer_reviews.author: Joan

customer_reviews.title: Nice size and look.
customer_reviews.text: I wish it was tall enough to have one small shelf at the top for odds and ends. I really like the height holds long handle tools. Holds a lot without being too bulky. I like the ivory gray color that blends in with natural wall coloring.
customer_reviews.author: Frequent Shopper

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed
customer_reviews.text: Usually very pleased with Rubbermaid products. However, I would not order this again. Not worth the price of $250.00 Side panel was warped and hinges on doors are plastic. Hinge broke 2 days after assembly.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: A Cinch to Assemble
customer_reviews.text: I am a senior adult female and I had no problem assembling this shed on my own on my patio. The directions were precise and easy to follow. It is the perfect size for the few garden tools and buckets that I needed to store for the lady who does my weeding. It makes my patio look much more organized to have gardening items out of the way.
customer_reviews.author: Susan Curtis

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for pool storage
customer_reviews.text: This item is not fully weatherproof on it's own. My husband made shelves & used silicone to seal everything. But the size was perfect for our space.
customer_reviews.author: L SUT

customer_reviews.title: Just what I was looking for
customer_reviews.text: Love it! Was easy to put together, all pieces are clearly marked...it's perfect for my upper deck storage needs.
customer_reviews.author: Myra

customer_reviews.title: Great for long handled tools
customer_reviews.text: I bought this for my husband’s birthday. He loves it and stored all his long handled tools in it and more!
customer_reviews.author: BOOK MAVEN

customer_reviews.title: The carton said the pieces slide together easily (BS). I have never use more profanity try ...
customer_reviews.text: No instructions were included! The carton said the pieces slide together easily (BS). I have never use more profanity try to get this storage unit together. The snaps won't snap. The design prevents any easy assembly of the top because a long rib on the top to the back blocked sliding it back into place. I used to hold Rubbermaid in high regard. What engineer designed this unit should be fired! You should be shamed of your self!
customer_reviews.author: S. Bonnet

customer_reviews.title: Exactly as presented
customer_reviews.text: Update review. Product is well make, but assembly is a tough for one person. Had problem with interlocking pieces. Wind was a problem when top came off, then sides. The interlocking just don't hole it together. I had to beef it up with screws, after the third time.
customer_reviews.author: Joe T.

customer_reviews.title: Extremely cheap, no hardware holding together
customer_reviews.text: This is a horrible product, fell apart after 3 weeks of use when the first Munro wins hit it, it has plastic pieces that fit into other molded plastic pieces, there is no hardware holding it together....and after it has collapsed into a big heap the plastic warps and does not fit back into the slots.... Do not buy this
customer_reviews.author: Mommabear

customer_reviews.title: Super Easy Assembly
customer_reviews.text: Everything just snaps together and then needs a few taps with a rubber mallet. Best done with an assistant. Very solid and satisfactory for keeping a small group of long handled garden tools and a few bags of soil organized. The weight of the soil in the bottom adds to the feeling of stability.
customer_reviews.author: Maria M. Thompson

customer_reviews.title: DOES NOT COME WITH SHELVES!
customer_reviews.text: Solid product, however highly disappointed it did not come with the shelves. The instructions/measurements were adequate however the extra steps to go to the store buy the shelving and then cut to size was not exactly what I had bargained for. the one place to get the shelves took a while for shipping. Disappointed that I spent the money and then had a bunch of extra steps to go through before I could use the product.
customer_reviews.author: Maggie Tyner

customer_reviews.title: Impossible to assemple by mere mortals
customer_reviews.text: This storage unit is almost impossible to assemble withut expert help. Maybe it would be easier if it had just come off the assembly line and was somewhat pliable. Or if you had lots of long clamps or 3 or 4 men to help. Too bad I tried several times and if it was deliverwed on time I could have returned it.
customer_reviews.author: Almaxxy

customer_reviews.title: Nice Storage
customer_reviews.text: This plastic vertical storage shed is perfect for storing gardening equipment and tools on my deck. It is nice looking, easy to assemble and made of tough heavy duty plastic material. I made only one shelf for the top since I mainly needed vertical space for several long handled tools: shovels, rake, etc. I placed it up against the wall of the house on the deck. I'm not sure how it would fare out in the yard unprotected. I would guess that a strong wind would move it unless it was anchored down. For what I needed however, it is perfect and a good value.
customer_reviews.author: dogbone

customer_reviews.title: Get the instructions before you try to install.
customer_reviews.text: Please don't do what it tried to do! The shed does not come with instructions, so I fussed with it and said more than a few unkind words about Rubbermaid. Then I downloaded the instructions and it took less than 10 minutes and it was installed. It looks easy to build and it is, but you must follow a sequence. Also, all prior comments about it being subject to blowing over are valid, so be sure to take that into consideration. The three stars are for the lack of instructions and no shelves.
customer_reviews.author: Gil Blumenthal

customer_reviews.title: Would buy again
customer_reviews.text: This is a great storage cabinet. Put it together in about 20 minutes. Had to cut shelves, but already knew that. It was packed well.
customer_reviews.author: Deborah G.

customer_reviews.title: Good product, but be ready for a puzzle.
customer_reviews.text: Seems to be made fairly well. I would have given five stars but it came with absolutely no paperwork, no instructions of any kind. I really didn't want a puzzle to figure out, but I got it together. Was hoping to receive a template for the shelves, but no such luck. Come on Rubbermade you can do better than that.
customer_reviews.author: Jeremy

customer_reviews.title: Really sturdy! Good quality!
customer_reviews.text: I was really surprised on the quality and sturdiness of this storage. It's was so easy to but together. We are currently using it for our sons baseball equipment works perfect. No leaks or dirt inside. Do recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Kray06

customer_reviews.title: Well build cabinet
customer_reviews.text: This cabinet is a really nice product - very easy to assemble and requires no tools. Recommend having 2 people do it because an extra set of hands makes it much easier. Like color and I like the storage space and the ability to add shelves (you have to make them yourself which is no problem if you are handy with a saw).
customer_reviews.author: Steve @ Lake Dragonfly

customer_reviews.title: Handsome compact size shed
customer_reviews.text: This is my 3rd Rubbermaid shed to be used outdoors. Hope it is as durable as the others. Looks fine for now. Will advise if any leaks as we go.
customer_reviews.author: Debra E. Dillon

customer_reviews.title: No assembly instructions
customer_reviews.text: I am pretty good at assembling things and found this challenging. I would suggest a ones sheet instructional sheet because the average person would find assembly difficult
customer_reviews.author: joseph  bryan

customer_reviews.title: Putting together was easy but NOT sturdy
customer_reviews.text: DO NOT BUY! I saw reviews with comments about the Rubbermaid Plastic Vertical Outdoor Storage unit coming apart during wind storm and decided they didn't put together correctly. I purchased with high hopes. Putting together was easy but NOT sturdy. To my surprise the first storm with wind the Rubbermaid Plastic Vertical Outdoor Storage completely came apart. This is my first unhappy experience with a Rubbermaid product. It's now laying on it's side in the backyard waiting for bulk trash pick up. What a waste of money.
customer_reviews.author: AZParrotLady

customer_reviews.title: You can get a padlock on it and lock it up.
customer_reviews.text: Perfect size for a small space. Easy to put together. I made shelves to fit the ledges. I can use the shelving otherwise it is just for up right tools like rakes, shovels, brooms etc.
customer_reviews.author: Debra A.

customer_reviews.title: Useful and sturdy enough
customer_reviews.text: This is working great for our needs. It was easy to put together and so far has held up (we've owned it for a summer). The inside is roomy enough for my yard tools and it is light enough that I can manipulate it or move it around on my own. We have had trouble finding flat ground for it and I am concerned that I will warp it or compromise the structural integrity due to that but I would say that is my problem not the manufacturers.
customer_reviews.author: Kelly Taylor

customer_reviews.title: Rubbermade Vertical Shed.
customer_reviews.text: This shed is the most disappointing purchase I have made from Amazon. The sides of the unit buckled within a month of assembly, allowing the shelves which I paid to have made, to fall spilling product in bottom of unit. Rubbermaid replaced the side panels and I paid a handyman to reassemble it and reinstall the shelves. Within a month the sides buckled again, and everything fell once more. I paid my handyman to drill holes on the outside and screw in the shelves which hold less than 10 pounds of product each. I have over $300.00 invested in this mistake.
customer_reviews.author: BonnieBrown

customer_reviews.title: Very Solid Cabinet
customer_reviews.text: Very solid - won't blow over like the one I replaced. You need to make your own shelves for this and the directions call for shelves that don't fill the whole space front to back (Maybe 2/3s of the way) and if you cut them too big they aren't supported.. so you waste a little space... so 4 stars not 5 for that reason...
customer_reviews.author: TJ C

customer_reviews.title: Be aware that titled dimensions are wrong!
customer_reviews.text: The shed is fine and generally easy to assemble but be advised that it is NOT 2x2x72 -- the Amazon title is misleading though the correct dimensions are given lower in the description. Unfortunately, DH did not notice the difference. If you are expecting it to fit in a tight space (as we were), you may be disappointed. We found another spot for it. If it had been titled correctly, I would have given it four stars.
customer_reviews.author: Suzanne

customer_reviews.title: Nice Cabinet: Easy to Assemble
customer_reviews.text: Nice outdoor cabinet. Took about 15 minutes to put together with the only tool being a mallet. Went to Home Depot and got wood cut for shelves. I still would like to screw the shelves into the walls for added stability, but that's a quickie project for a future afternoon.
customer_reviews.author: Paul W.

customer_reviews.title: Nice cabinet.
customer_reviews.text: This cabinet is perfect for storing our BBQ supplies in on the deck. It does not come with shelves although there are notches in the sides to support them. We just made a template and cut them out of plywood. That way we could do as many as we wanted. We made two so that we'd have a taller space in the bottom of the cabinet. It's sturdy and is relatively easy to assemble...Assemble it laying on it's back! Don't try to stand it up to assemble.
customer_reviews.author: C. thayer

customer_reviews.title: Love it.
customer_reviews.text: I've had it for just under a month and I love this. We keep it on the pool deck as it hides a lot of ugly pool care items and it works great. I would suggest that when you have the shelves cut maybe go just a little big. Those that were cut for me matched the measurements given in the directions and they slip out on one side or the other pretty easily - may end up having to "adapt" them a bit as a result.
customer_reviews.author: Lisa

customer_reviews.title: Lightweight but sturdy
customer_reviews.text: It is very lightweight but we put wooden shelves in it and weighed it down with some patio blocks. Our first summer storm it blow away and disassembled but now it stays in place and work great .
customer_reviews.author: Beth Hopper

customer_reviews.title: Easy
customer_reviews.text: Easy Assembly. Love how Rubbermaid embossed the part name like “left lateral side panel” directly onto the part itself. Nice fits with no tools. I opted to install shelves {not included) and you can rely on the dimensions shown on schematic. I’m happy.
customer_reviews.author: Buzz Wagner

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble, looks good, provides a good amount of storage space.
customer_reviews.text: Easy to assemble and is like an extra pantry for my patio deck. Does not come with shelves; however, you can build your own with specifications from the manufacturer. I built four of my own shelves for about $10 in lumber from Home Depot. I highly recommend this product.
customer_reviews.author: IATFalcon

customer_reviews.title: Busted latch
customer_reviews.text: I gave this 2 stars because within a month the the circular pad lock latch busted off. Other than that it was perfect
customer_reviews.author: Lyssa M. Orelli

customer_reviews.title: Very easy to assemble
customer_reviews.text: Arrived promptly. Easy to assemble with two people, about 15 minutes. I sliced my hand on a jagged edge of the plastic material near one of the hinges. I suggest caution while unpacking and assembling. Overall I am very pleased with my shed.
customer_reviews.author: laura b.

customer_reviews.title: Easy to put together
customer_reviews.text: I love the looks of it! Simple to put together. It also matches a couple of other storage containers the I use for outdoor cushions.
customer_reviews.author: Darlene N.

customer_reviews.title: Really good buy!
customer_reviews.text: I've had my eye on this shed for awhile and couldn't resist the "Daily Deal" price. A friend of mine put it together in about 1/2 hr. Everything fit and it opens with no problems. It's too bad about the lack of shelving, but there must have been weight problems with the same material the outside is made of. Instructions are included, but a lady who commented here really helped me out. The shed fits on my outdoor patio (I have a really small apartment unit) and is just what I expected. Bought it for the Rubbermaid name and am not disappointed!
customer_reviews.author: SKM17

customer_reviews.title: Just add Silicone
customer_reviews.text: Bought this to hold the ever growing amount of BBQ accessories that are spread out around my place. After reading the reviews about how this unit can come apart when the wind blows or when moving, I used a tube of 100% silicone while assembling. I put some in all the joints when I assembled as well as a bead all the way around the inside after assembly. I did this a week or so before moving out of the garage allowing the silicone to cure. This unit now seems solid and secure.
customer_reviews.author: Woody

customer_reviews.title: Keeps stuff dry, as long as...
customer_reviews.text: it doesnt fall apart. This does a fairly good job keeping tools in one place, but if you are too rough with it, it will come apart. In fact, after one day opening and closing it in a not very crisp way, I went out to find that the wind had blown it apart. That may have been an assembly problem, since it only has happened once, but even now that we have been doing some spring gardening and opening and closing it a lot as we select different tools, its starting to look like I might have to take it apart and reassemble it so that the walls and doors are properly aligned.
customer_reviews.author: Sam Mercer

customer_reviews.title: the "snapping" together is not a great design, I have it sitting on a concrete ...
customer_reviews.text: I have owned this since June 2014... I can not count the time I have put it back together.. everytime I open the door it falls apart, the wind blows to hard and it falls apart.. the "snapping" together is not a great design, I have it sitting on a concrete slab on my patio and well its useless and frustrating. Find something else to purchase if you actually want to use it, if your just storing stuff you will never use again it is fine.
customer_reviews.author: Denise J. Knox

customer_reviews.title: Good construction. Easy to assemble
customer_reviews.text: Good construction. Easy to assemble. However, if you want shelves buy a shed with shelves. I had to go to Home Depot, buy an entire sheet of plywood, have them cut the shelves. But they don't do diagonal cuts. So I have to do it myself. Additional cost: $40.00 for plywood (and they'd will resale the 3/4 of the board I don't need.).
customer_reviews.author: Candace Hadley

customer_reviews.title: Just what I wanted and went together easily
customer_reviews.text: This is just the size I wanted and went together easily. All my yard tools (tall ones) fit in it. Now I just have to see how it holds up in a Georgia summer ! I have it under an overhang, so it will be protected from direct sun.
customer_reviews.author: Suzanne Joyce

customer_reviews.title: So happy with this purchase
customer_reviews.text: So happy with this purchase. I wanted to store long handled rakes, shovels, clippers near where I use them the most and this was perfect for my needs. Delivery was fast and assembly took less than 10 minutes. READ the description and realize before you order that shelves are not included! I am sure that this will last for a very long time similar to other Rubbermaid products made from the same material.
customer_reviews.author: Jena

customer_reviews.title: Well designed, easy to assemble
customer_reviews.text: Fed Ex delivered this and it was put together and in use in 15 minutes. No tools needed. Just snaps together. I went to Home Depot and bought a piece of plywood and cut two shelves. Approx, 27.75" x 9" and notch the corner at around 3" for the angle cut. Note, the shelves are narrow! They are not designed to come all the way to the front. This is actually OK so that you can out shovels rakes etc in front of the shelves. Well designed unit and I'm happy with it. I may get another.
customer_reviews.author: West LA Guy

customer_reviews.title: This shed went together really easily. It serves my purpose well enough and I ...
customer_reviews.text: This shed went together really easily. It serves my purpose well enough and I guess it's what I expected. I think it's a little expensive for what it is, but how long it last will determine whether or not it was worth the money.
customer_reviews.author: Mme Cruz

customer_reviews.title: Dont buy: very bad packaging comes open and items damaged
customer_reviews.text: I ordered two of them. They arrived, packaged really bad, open on each side, cardboard torn apart. I didnt have time to check for damages on the cabinets yet, but its likely they are damaged, and if I have to return them I will have to pay for new packaging. I will post pictures once I get to it. Sorry I couln not give zero stars.
customer_reviews.author: Chris

customer_reviews.title: Just what we needed.
customer_reviews.text: This is just what we needed for storage for our rakes, shovels, and other items that were constantly falling down and simply discouraging having them in the garage. This unit was simple to put together. My husband wasn't home and I was able to put it together by myself, even though it was large and bulky. It's amazing what a simple storage unit can do to relieve stress in the garage. We now know exactly where those items are and they're out of the way when we're not using them!
customer_reviews.author: WiseMom

customer_reviews.title: Good item for the price!
customer_reviews.text: For the money, this is a good product with limited space. A user can fabricate shelves if they wish, but I decided to use it for yard tools instead. Did not bother to read directions for assembly. However, if you are not familiar with items such as these, reviewing assembly instructions might be useful. Undoubtedly, you will need a rubber mallet to "seat" the floor panel into the back panel.
customer_reviews.author: Paul T. Klenk

customer_reviews.title: Slide it together in 5 minutes!!
customer_reviews.text: This is a great shed for my small patio. It holds all the tools I need for my small garden. The best thing is that this took 5 minutes to put together. It slides together, nothing is needed but a plastic hammer to wedge the parts together. No screw driver or screws, just the ability to lift the piece and push together. The lock piece is already installed. Great for apartment and condo owners!
customer_reviews.author: Kathryn L. Bales

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy and easy to assemble !
customer_reviews.text: Very pleased. Easy to assemble. Just right for storing my garden tools. Sturdy built. We put it at the side of our house so I don't have to go to the basement to get the weed eater, blower and rake. Love it
customer_reviews.author: debbieinhickory

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble, looks good.
customer_reviews.text: So easy to put together and looks very good. I purchased a 12' x 12" board and cut 4 shelves which were easy to install. I use it to put my small tools; ie drill, reciprocating saw, etc, screws, nails etc. in. I placed it on my screened-in porch .. it looks good. I am very pleased with it.
customer_reviews.author: Bonnie Whittington

customer_reviews.title: Don't buy it!
customer_reviews.text: Don't buy this piece of crap storage container. I've had mine for 4 weeks and it's already falling apart. The plastic is coming apart at the seams and won't stay attached. I have it sitting outside on the side of the house away from the afternoon sun and the plastic still softened up and came apart. I'm outside of the return window by 2 days so I guess I'm stuck with it and will end up throwing it away.
customer_reviews.author: Lilian

customer_reviews.title: Great Storage for the space challenged.
customer_reviews.text: This is a very nice little storage unit and larger than it looks on screen. I store a lot of chemicals in milk crates and they fit well side by side in this storage with a bit of room in front for rakes, brooms and weedeaters.This would make a very nice storage for a smaller generator and gas cans, or a reel mower, etc. I got this item on a gold box deal for about a benjamin and I wish I had bought two of them.
customer_reviews.author: Drue J. Deshotels

customer_reviews.title: Barebones Storage
customer_reviews.text: Takes about 10 minutes to put this storage container together, pieces fit reasonably well, and it is very handsomely priced. However, the bottom panel is not weighted, meaning you will need to put something heavy in the bottom (I used some buckets of outdoor paint) or otherwise connect this item to the ground/slab or it will be blown over by heavy winds. There are also no shelves, though there are grooves for shelving inside the unit. This is honestly nothing more than five pieces of plastic with a door on the front - but the price is right, making it an OK purchase in my book.
customer_reviews.author: MaskedMaru

customer_reviews.title: Very convenient storage
customer_reviews.text: Great place to store things in the yard without having to give up a lot of room. However, note that it doesn't come with shelves anymore. Have to ask Rubbermaid, why not? who makes an upright storage container without any shelves? Having said that, my husband made the shelves and I still like the size and shape.
customer_reviews.author: Loves to read...

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed
customer_reviews.text: This Rubbermaid product is extremely inferior and disappointing. It is of flimsy construction and no where near being weatherproof. Additionally, the 'lock' if you can call it that, is so flimsy anyone could easily pull off a padlock. Buyers, beware.
customer_reviews.author: Cathy Frazier

customer_reviews.title: Easy to put together
customer_reviews.text: The product was easy to put together and the shelves were easy to cut. Don’t spend more than $20 for shelving
customer_reviews.author: Steven B.

customer_reviews.title: I can't get out my front door!!!
customer_reviews.text: I am very tiffed about the delivery person blocking my front door to get outside. I'm sure the actual product will be fine if I could only get to it I have pictures of this blockage but I can't figure out how to load them on here. What a hassle
customer_reviews.author: Rebecca L.

customer_reviews.title: Very good with some annoyances
customer_reviews.text: This is indeed a very good product as reported here by other reviewers. My major complaint is that there were no instructions in the box as listed on the parts list. A simple numbered illustration (similar to those that IKEA provides) would have sufficed to save time. Of course, the next one will go together in perhaps 5 minutes! The other gripe is as others have reported - there are no shelves. OK, so I'll make some, but a simple diagram with cutout dimensions would be user-friendly touch and time saver. I will probably purchase another one.
customer_reviews.author: D. Coppell

customer_reviews.title: Good value for the cost.
customer_reviews.text: I really think this was a good buy. I added shelves by just cutting some wood boards to fit, I would have given 5 stars if it came with them. Aesthetically, I couldn't go any bigger but this holds almost all of my gardening/indoor potting supplies now that I have the shelves. This includes my push-mower, 2 shovels, and a maddock on the floor under the shelves. If it was a couple inches wider though I would be able to cram more in the bottom because I do need to angle the mower to get it in and out.
customer_reviews.author: J.S.

customer_reviews.title: Great Quality!
customer_reviews.text: Works Well, protects from the rain and snow! Glad I finallly bought it ! I had to watch it for a while until it went on sale, I’m cheap ! But this Shed isn’t !
customer_reviews.author: Gabryl D McAlester

customer_reviews.title: Quality construction
customer_reviews.text: I was a little disappointed with this vertical shed. While the quality of construction is good the unit tends to be a little wobbly unless you put something heavy in the bottom of it for stability. The lack of shelves limits the practical use of space, but adding shelves would limit the ability to store tall/long items, which is what I purchased it for in the first place. I'm giving it 3 stars as it is probably a good choice for someone who has the sort of items that will effectively use the space and appreciate the quality of construction.
customer_reviews.author: Dave P

customer_reviews.title: Great shed
customer_reviews.text: I was lucky enough to get this storage shed when it was a daily deal, but I feel it would have been worth even the regular price. My kids (and 4 and 6) and I put it together in 5 minutes. I'm not sure why anyone said it was difficult. It's got plenty of room, seems very durable and it's going to be perfect for what I need it for. I kind of wish it had shelves but I bought it knowing that it didn't come with any. Super happy with this purchase. Thanks!
customer_reviews.author: renshawclan

customer_reviews.title: Decent outdoor shed
customer_reviews.text: It assembled easily, and seems to stay together fine (make sure you press the pieces together until you hear a "pop" sound, otherwise they will fall apart). I would have liked more options for shelving, but I had to resort to cutting my own. I purchased some standard 3/4" coated chipboard shelving and cut it. The shelf space is not rectangular-- some diagonal cuts on the back corners will help for a good fit, but you'll need some basic tools and a reasonable place to do the cutting.
customer_reviews.author: Stephen

customer_reviews.title: Rubbermaid verticals storage shed
customer_reviews.text: Nice shed. Easy to put together for pieces just snap together using a mallet. Took about 20 minutes to put together with my daughter holding the pieces while I banged them in place with the rubber mallet. Shelves are not included. We use the shed for tall items like shovels and brooms. We put the shed in our garage. Not sure how waterproof this would be if put outside because the top piece would not snap on without a tiny gap on each side. Overall good quality for the money.
customer_reviews.author: Fran B

customer_reviews.title: too small for the money
customer_reviews.text: Height is good but very narrow and does not hold enough. If it were cheaper it would be worth it.
customer_reviews.author: Optimus Prime

customer_reviews.title: Skeptical of durability
customer_reviews.text: This shed serves its purpose but the assembly has absolutely no hardware. This makes me skeptical of how it will hold up to wind and weather. To be determined. My sister and I assembled it in 15 minutes. The price seems steep for what you get.
customer_reviews.author: Kelsey Carson

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble, strong construction.
customer_reviews.text: I use this for storing my yard tools and my 16" push mower. I used the built in ridges to install some shelves. I only wish there were an easy way to install some hooks from the ceiling without poking a hole in the roof. All in all though, a great buy. I may get another one for the other side of the house to store crap wood in.
customer_reviews.author: C. Girard

customer_reviews.title: This is the third unit like this, which means I like them
customer_reviews.text: This is the third unit like this, which means I like them. Great for outdoor stuff. Keeps the stuff organized and out of the elements. The first unit was dented. Amazon replaced it quickly. I am completely satisfied.
customer_reviews.author: Jerald M. Savin

customer_reviews.title: Very happy with this purchase
customer_reviews.text: Very happy with this purchase. Everything went together quickly once the pieces were laid out in the lawn. Used a rubber mallet to easily snap things in place. The measurement worked perfectly for the 3 shelves we cut. We put it by the carport, for outdoor supplies like lawnmower oil, starter spray, lawn tools, and plant fertilizer, etc. It is great for keeping down clutter.
customer_reviews.author: Rose

customer_reviews.title: compact fits nicely against house
customer_reviews.text: felt cost was a little high. use it for long handle tools easy to assemble
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy, and waterproof
customer_reviews.text: It should come with optional shelves, I did make them out of wood though. Overall, this is a very sturdy water proof cabinet.
customer_reviews.author: Wallace Carl Ferguson

customer_reviews.title: Good Product
customer_reviews.text: I bought two of these sheds to replace 1 bigger shed we lost in a flood. Buying two smaller sheds provides same space of a larger shed and provides me the option of placing one shed at a different location. High quality, easy assemble. I assembled it in about 30 minutes. You have to provide your own shelves. That was simple. I took the shelve measurements, went to Home Depot and they cut me 8 shelves (4 for each shed). Love the Product
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great product, great company!
customer_reviews.text: I bought this about a year ago and it has been outside my little home all that time. It is easy to put together, sturdy, & weather resistant, through East Texas thunderstorms, snow, hail, and the like. When I bought it, it had one misshapen door. I called rubbermaid direct and they remedied the situation immediatley!! I had a new, perfect door within a few days. No hassles. Not often you find that kind of customer service anymore. Overall, would recommend this product.
customer_reviews.author: Cedar Grove Ranch

customer_reviews.title: Shelves not included.
customer_reviews.text: Why did you show all those images WITH SHELVES, but the unit doesn't come with shelves. Not only that, it will take a CARPENTER to manufacture the Correct Shelves. You could have at the very LEAST, made it CONSPICUOUS that Shelves were NOT Included, then gave the proper Measurements to manufacture shelves. A disappointment for sure.
customer_reviews.author: Stacy

customer_reviews.title: No Shelves
customer_reviews.text: Easy to assemble however there are no shelves which has a caused a problem for me and I'm certainly not handy enough to make shelves as suggested in another review.
customer_reviews.author: Katie

customer_reviews.title: Good Storage Cabinet
customer_reviews.text: This is more of a storage cabinet than a shed. It arrived on schedule and I had it assembled in about 10 minutes. I use it to store the spa chemicals and misc. equipment. It seems sturdy enough, but will tip over in the wind if you do not keep it next to the wall. The interior has molded ledges for 4 shelves. I purchased a 10' 1x10; Lowe's cut it into 4ea 28 3/4" shelves for free. I had to cut the corners and the shelves slipped in the slots. Good cabinet for my purpose.
customer_reviews.author: Ol' Man

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy and easy to assemble.
customer_reviews.text: Easy to assemble, very strong. Only down side is I cant find a lock that can fit through the hole.
customer_reviews.author: Steve

customer_reviews.title: outdoor storage
customer_reviews.text: This is exactly what I was looking for to store my grilling accessories
customer_reviews.author: Jeff L

customer_reviews.title: Convenient storage!
customer_reviews.text: So easy to assemble and just the perfect size for yard tools and extra propane tank. And looks great in side yard.
customer_reviews.author: Robert Macias

customer_reviews.title: Does not included any shelves and none are available from ...
customer_reviews.text: Does not included any shelves and none are available from Rubbermaid. Apparently "making" them from wood that does not match the shed is the only solution. Not impressive.
customer_reviews.author: Gregory Teachman

customer_reviews.title: Nails and lumber nextime.
customer_reviews.text: The shed came as a warped bunch of panels that didn't slide in very well. When finally assembled there were gaps you could put your hand in. The lock is a joke so we we wont place anything worth much in it.Rubbermaid blew it big on this contraption.Waste of plastic.
customer_reviews.author: zip427

customer_reviews.title: is still in perfect condition! It sits on the patio
customer_reviews.text: We have owned this shed for almost 4 years, we live in Colorado so this shed experiences every type of weather condition and heavy periods of wind, is still in perfect condition! It sits on the patio, gets a healthy amount of sun and still looks great!! Only complaint? Wish shelves were available so I didn't have to got out and make my own out of wood. Just got a new hot tub, going to add towel hooks and a shelf and turn it into a spa cabinet!!!
customer_reviews.author: JA

This outdoor storage shed is easy to assemble and is leak-, dent- and weather-resistant. With 17 cu. ft. of space, easily store long-handled tools such as rakes and brooms. Storage unit can also be locked for security (lock not included). Includes heavy-duty, impact-resistant floor mat.
